<SO>
WALL STREET JOURNAL (J), NO PAGE CITATION
</SO>
<CO>
   DRSDY
</CO>
<IN>
DIVIDENDS (DIV)
</IN>
<LP>
   FRANKFURT, West Germany -- Dresdner Bank AG said it has
decided to boost its annual cash dividend for 1989 to 12
marks (US$7) a share from 10 marks paid for the previous
year.
   The second-largest West German banking group last raised
it dividend in 1985, when the annual payout rose from 7.5
marks a share.
</LP>
