<LP>
   CINCINNATI -- Comair Holdings Inc. said passenger
boardings at its Comair Inc. airline rose 30% in March to
164,893 passengers, from 126,735 a year earlier.
   Revenue passenger miles jumped 40% to 32.9 million, from
23.5 million in March 1989, Comair said. The carrier filled
44.5% of the available seats, down from 45.6% in the year
earlier month.
</LP>
<TEXT>
   For the fiscal year ended March 31, passenger boardings
increased 28% to 1.6 million, and revenue passenger miles
climbed 32% to 305.6 million. Comair filled 44.7% of
available seats during the latest year, up from 42.3% in
fiscal 1989.
   A revenue passenger mile is a paying passenger transported
one mile.
